%% Multi-Agent Framework — agent communication, execution flow, state flow,
%% and workflow lifecycle (docs/adr/0009-multi-agent-framework-shape.md).
%% Render with `mmdc -i multi-agent-framework.mmd -o multi-agent-framework.png`.
%% No specialist agent exists yet — "SpecialistAgent(s)" below is what
%% Milestone M1+ adds by registering into AgentRegistry and
%% core/graph/investigation_graph.py; nothing else on this diagram changes.

sequenceDiagram
    participant Caller as core/services (future)
    participant Engine as WorkflowEngine
    participant Coord as CoordinatorAgent
    participant Plan as PlanningAgent
    participant Router as router.route_from_coordinator
    participant Spec as SpecialistAgent(s)
    participant State as CaseInvestigationState

    Caller->>Engine: run(state)
    Engine->>State: execution_scope(case_id, run_id)
    Engine->>Coord: coordinator node (state)
    Coord->>Plan: direct call, not a graph edge
    Plan->>State: read metadata.required_capabilities
    Plan->>State: write execution_plan (ExecutionPlan)
    Plan-->>Coord: state (mutated)
    Coord-->>Engine: state (mutated), diffed against pre-node snapshot
    Engine->>Router: route_from_coordinator(state)
    Router-->>Engine: [specialist_a, specialist_b] or [END]

    par fan-out (one LangGraph superstep)
        Engine->>Spec: specialist_a node (private deep copy of state)
        Spec->>State: append findings / thoughts (on its own copy)
        Spec-->>Engine: diff vs. original state
    and
        Engine->>Spec: specialist_b node (private deep copy of state)
        Spec->>State: append findings / thoughts (on its own copy)
        Spec-->>Engine: diff vs. original state
    end

    Engine->>State: merge diffs via Annotated reducers (operator.add / dict-merge)
    Engine-->>Caller: final CaseInvestigationState

    Note over Engine,State: Every node invocation also publishes<br/>AGENT_STARTED/COMPLETED/FAILED events<br/>(core/graph/events.py) consumed by<br/>MetricsCollector and structlog_listener.
    Note over Engine: On an unhandled exception escaping<br/>a node, RetryPolicy retries transient<br/>failures; FailureRecoveryPolicy converts<br/>an exhausted failure into requires_manual_triage<br/>rather than crashing the run.
